<article
  xmlns:ev='http://www.w3.org/2001/xml-events'
  xmlns:xforms="http://www.w3.org/2002/xforms"
  xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:xxforms="http://orbeon.org/oxf/xml/xforms"
>
  <title>The MathDox Formula Editor</title>
  <section>
    <title>Entering mathematics</title>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>Easy to use: WYSIWYG and intuitive</listitem>
      <listitem>Produces a semantic representation: OpenMath</listitem>
      <listitem>No plugins needed, not using JAVA</listitem>
      <listitem>Easily to integrate</listitem>
      <listitem>Open Source License (LGPL)</listitem>
      <listitem>Easy to extend or to adapt</listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>
  <section>
    <title>Current status</title>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>A lot of symbols are supported</listitem>
      <listitem>Easy to extend with new keywords and also possible to use prefix
      	notation for unknown symbols</listitem>
      <listitem>Fairly easy to add new complicated symbols</listitem>
      <listitem>Optional palette, which is easy to customize</listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>
  <section>
    <title>Future work</title>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>Better documentation</listitem>
      <listitem>More output formats (like CAS native languages)</listitem>
      <listitem>Movable palette</listitem>
      <listitem>Selection, copy, paste, undo</listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>
</article>
